"It's a beautiful and big tree. Saku has never seen anything
like it before."\n<Saku>\F[5]\AA[FF]\FF[28]

"Yes... And I can feel a very clear power emanating from
this tree. It's repelling the curse only around here, which
is really strange. I wonder why."\n<Yukine>\F[4]\AA[F]\FF[28]
"Thank you for reading me a storybook."
"I'm happy to see my little sister."
"Yukine, I love you so much, please stay healthy."

"Ah, I see. This tree... it's inhabited by the feelings of
those who have been purified. It's so clear because it's
filled with gratitude and happiness."\n<Yukine>\F[1]

"Um... is this tree so lively because... Yukine Onee-san has
helped so many spirits... is that it?"\n<Saku>\F[1]\AA[FF]\FF[22]

("So that's it. The things we've done weren't in vain. But
it doesn't seem to be blooming well. Surely, human feelings
alone aren't enough.")\FF[22]\F[7]\AA[F]
"Um... if I share my fertility power like this, maybe..."\n<Yukine>\F[4]

The great tree, having received divine energy, regained its
vitality, and Saku's doll, touched by the gentle wind, began
to glow faintly.\AA[N]\F[16]\FF[28]
"Yukine Onee-san, Saku... it seems like we're being called."\n<Saku>\F[8]\AA[FF]\FF[24]

"It's okay, I'm fine. Mom says to come inside... so I'm
going to go."\n<Saku>\F[16]\AA[FF]\FF[40]

"Saku! I was so surprised... I was worried when you went

"Welcome back. Huh... Saku? Your body... it's warm."\n<Yukine>\F[5]\AA[F]\FF[63]

"Yeah, and somehow... my body feels a bit heavy."\n<Saku>\F[5]\AA[FF]\FF[60]
"Yeah, and somehow... my body feels a bit heavy."\n<Saku>\F[5]\AA[FF]\FF[22]

"Eh... um, does this mean... you've returned to your

"Now we just need to get out of here. It's not much longer,

"...So you've reclaimed Saku's body. How insolent of mere
human spirits to defy me. This must be the work of that fox
child. She's done something unnecessary."\n<Saku Disaster Moon>

"Well, no matter. If it was taken, I just need to take it
back... ..."\n<Saku Disaster Moon>
"Saku... you belong to me. I won't let you escape."\n<Saku Disaster Moon>
(I feel like I've left something undone)

"Saku, what are you dissatisfied with? This is the eternal
home you wished for. Why do you destroy my domain?"\n<Saku Disaster Moon>\FF[31]
"God, I don't like it here. It's dark, cold, and scary."\n<Saku>\FF[62]
"God, I don't like it here. It's dark, cold, and scary."\n<Saku>\FF[23]

"Then, I shall light a fire. If you wish for freedom, I
shall grant it, and I will stay by Saku's side as much as
she desires."\n<Saku Disaster Moon>\FF[31]

"Saku has been lonely and wanted to go home... I didn't want
my father or mother to die... I wanted them to live."\n<Saku>\FF[62]

"Saku has been lonely and wanted to go home... I didn't want
my father or mother to die... I wanted them to live."\n<Saku>\FF[23]

"If you die, we can be together forever. What is there to be
dissatisfied about hastening the inevitable separation?"\n<Saku Disaster Moon>\FF[39]

"Saku Kagetsuki... Humans are meant to be surrounded by the
living. Filling one's heart with the dead does not lead to
happiness."\n<Yukine>\F[4]

"Silence! How dare a mere fox like you offer opinions to me.
Know your place!"\n<Saku Disaster Moon>\FF[37]

"What do you know? The pain of being abandoned and
forgotten, a pampered Inari deity from the human world could
never understand!"\n<Saku Disaster Moon>\FF[37]

"Saku Kagetsuki. I may not understand your feelings... But
loneliness is no excuse to bind someone and take away their
freedom."\n<Yukine>\F[18]

"Silence, fox! How dare you steal Saku from me and ravage my
garden. I will not let you live any longer. You shall become
an eternal sacrifice for the mansion."\n<Saku Disaster Moon>\FF[37]

"(Such powerful curse energy... But it's not as oppressive
as before. It must be weakened since we destroyed the
mansion's keystone.)"\n<Yukine>\F[55]
(Saku seems to be at her limit.)\FF[21]\F[4]\AA[F]
(I feel like I could fight now if I had to.)\F[8]

(I feel like I could fight now if I had to, but maybe it's
better to run away with Saku.)\F[8]
"Saku, do you want to be free?"\n<Yukine>\F[4]
"Yes. Saku wants to be with Yukine Onee-san."\n<Saku>\F[4]\AA[FF]\FF[62]
"Yes. Saku wants to be with Yukine Onee-san."\n<Saku>\F[4]\AA[FF]\FF[23]
"Saku... Are you also abandoning me? Even you..."\n<Saku Disaster Moon>\FF[37]

"No! Saku is mine. You will live here for all eternity. I'd
rather die than hand you over to a fox!"\n<Saku Disaster Moon>\FF[37]
"As I thought, you protected her!"\n<Saku Disaster Moon>\FF[32]

Sakuragetsu sneers with a grin. The cursed god knew what I
was trying to protect and deliberately targeted Saku.

Imbuing his hands with a malevolent power, Sakuragetsu
thrusts a sharp hand blade with murderous intent at me--

Despite clutching the amulet tightly, my wish did not reach.
A small hand pierced through my chest.

A scream echoes, and something hot spreads inside my chest.
My body trembles with the realization that something that
should not have broken has shattered, and the sensation of
life fading away--

Mocking me as I reached out to the precious girl, Sakugatsu
pulls her arm out.

And without waiting for a last word, the cursed god crushes
the divine core, now like a mangled tomato, in her grasp.

In my darkening vision, I see Sakugatsu swallowing the
shrunken heart. And as I fall, Saku's scream reaches my
ears.
But there's nothing I can do.

As if mocking my attempt to defend myself with a small
knife, Saku's fingertips swirled, making a slicing sound as
they passed by my neck.

I feel something cold on my neck, and a moment later, bright
red blood spurts from my throat.
"Big sis... no, it's a lie... this has to be a lie, right?"\n<Saku>

You can hear Saku's voice. However, with my throat slashed,
I can't even respond.

I can clearly feel my life fading away. The blood gushing
out turns into particles of spiritual energy and vanishes.

"To think you could deceive me, you're five hundred years
too early, vixen!"\n<Saku Disaster Moon>

In the end, thinking of Saku until the last moment, my head
was severed by those small hands.

I unsheathed the small knife in my hand and swung its rusty
blade.

The blade, which should have been rusty, swept away the
approaching tentacles, and Saku Kagetsuki, who lost
everything beyond her wrist, screamed.

Upon closer inspection, the blade that was covered in red
rust had turned to shining silver, faintly glowing. The
light, like a flame, was a gentle color as if to protect
Saku.\FF[66]\F[4]\AA[N]

"Grr, you used my power to turn back the time of the spirit
sword... To exorcise my power is detestable."\n<Saku Disaster Moon>\FF[72]

"Ugh, my power is fading... If it comes to this, I will
escape to the present world first."\n<Saku Disaster Moon>\FF[72]
"Uuuu... why only me... I just wanted... with Saku... grr."\n<Saku Disaster Moon>\FF[72]

"She intends to flee to the present world. Saku, we must
hurry! Or we won't be able to return."\n<Yukine>\F[19]

"Okay, I understand. Yukine Onee-san... But the deity
seemed... somehow lonely."\n<Saku>\F[19]\AA[FF]\FF[62]
(I understand that feeling too... But we need to hurry now.)\F[10]
"Haa haa... ugh... let's go. We have to return... together."\n<Saku>\F[19]\AA[FF]\FF[24]

(It seems like Saku is at her limit. I must defeat Saku
Kagetsuki quickly or this child's body won't last. We need
to chase after her immediately.)\F[8]

"Lady Yukine, please jump in! We can't reach the path to the
present world, but we've created a shortcut by bundling
together the faith towards the deity. Please hurry!"\n<Fox>\AA[N]\F[18]

"Do you think you can escape from me, vixen!"\n<Saku Disaster Moon>\FF[37]

"It's the end for you, vixen!"\n<Saku Disaster Moon>\FF[33]

The "rusty short sword" shattered under the black curse.

"Now's the time, Saku. Can you still run?"\n<Yukine>\F[4]\AA[F]\FF[23]
"Yes, I can... hah, mmm... I'm okay."\n<Saku>\F[4]\AA[FF]\FF[24]

"Let's go, Saku. I won't let go of your hand, I promise!"\n<Yukine>\F[4]\AA[F]\FF[24]
